'''Xolok''': Also known as ''Xoloc'', ''Xolos'', ''Xoloq'', and ''Xolon''.

Is a derogatory term used for Chechnyans since the May 6th, 2006 incident in a Russian
newspaper where many suspected rebels were said to be former agricultural workers. The term 
was previously benign and used in Cyrillic as a way to describe loyal farm servitude, but as of 
recent has gained international scorn due to the said article. The editor who added the piece 
has had his name protected due to a good deal of threats. 

Also considered to be a somewhat anti-Muslim term.

